    };

This `.then` and `.catch` methods return a new promise which is resolved or rejected via the return value (or throw) of the `successCallback`, `errorCallback` (unless that value is a promise, in which case it is resolved with the value which is resolved in that promise using [promise chaining](http://www.html5rocks.com/en/tutorials/es6/promises/#toc-promises-queues).

